sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Admin
    participant Panel as AgentsPanel
    participant Modal as CreateAgentModal
    participant Editor as Multi-tab Agent Editor
    participant API as AugmentApi
    participant BE as augment-backend<br/>adminConfigRoutes
    participant ACS as AdminConfigService<br/>agents + chatAgents
    participant RCR as RuntimeConfigResolver
    participant Graph as AgentGraphManager
    participant Orch as OpenAIAgentsOrchestrator
    participant LS as Llama Stack<br/>/v1/responses

    rect rgb(224, 231, 255)
        Note over Admin,Modal: Step 1 - Create New Agent
        Admin->>Panel: Click "New Agent"
        Panel->>Modal: Open CreateAgentModal
        Modal->>Modal: Show template presets
        Note over Modal: Templates:<br/>- Blank Agent<br/>- Code Assistant (code interpreter + web search)<br/>- Research Agent (RAG + web search)<br/>- Knowledge Expert (RAG only)
        Admin->>Modal: Enter name, select template
        Modal->>Modal: Auto-generate ID from name
        Modal->>Panel: onCreate(name, id)
        Panel->>Panel: Create agent with template defaults
    end

    rect rgb(209, 250, 229)
        Note over Admin,Editor: Step 2 - Configure Agent
        Panel->>Editor: Show multi-tab editor
        Note over Editor: Instructions Tab:<br/>- System prompt (markdown)<br/>- AI-assisted prompt generation<br/>- Model selection

        Note over Editor: Capabilities Tab:<br/>- MCP servers (multi-select)<br/>- Enable RAG + vector store IDs<br/>- Enable web search<br/>- Enable code interpreter<br/>- Handoff targets

        Note over Editor: Connections Tab:<br/>- Handoffs: [agent-key-1, agent-key-2]<br/>- asTools: [agent-key-3]<br/>- Auto-derived role: router / specialist / standalone

        Note over Editor: Advanced Tab:<br/>- Temperature, max tokens<br/>- Tool choice (auto/required/none)<br/>- Reasoning (enabled + summary)<br/>- Guardrails list<br/>- Max tool calls<br/>- Truncation strategy
    end

    rect rgb(237, 233, 254)
        Note over Admin,ACS: Step 3 - Save Configuration
        Admin->>Panel: Click Save
        Panel->>Panel: validateAgents(allAgents)
        Panel->>Panel: agentToConfig(formData) per agent
        Note over Panel: Builds Record of AgentConfig:<br/>{ router: { name, instructions,<br/>handoffs: [specialist-1], ... },<br/>specialist-1: { name, instructions,<br/>mcpServers: [server-id], ... } }

        Panel->>API: PUT /admin/config/agents
        API->>BE: Save agents config
        BE->>ACS: set('agents', agentConfigs)
        ACS->>ACS: Upsert to augment_admin_config

        BE->>BE: Auto-manage chatAgents entries
        Note over BE: For each router/standalone agent:<br/>- Create chatAgents entry if missing<br/>- lifecycleStage: pending<br/>For specialists: hide from catalog

        BE->>ACS: set('chatAgents', updatedConfigs)

        Panel->>API: PUT /admin/config/defaultAgent
        API->>BE: Save entry agent key
        BE->>ACS: set('defaultAgent', 'router')

        Panel->>API: PUT /admin/config/maxAgentTurns
        API->>BE: Save turn limit
        BE->>ACS: set('maxAgentTurns', 10)

        BE-->>Panel: Success
        Panel->>Admin: Show save confirmation
    end

    rect rgb(254, 243, 199)
        Note over RCR,LS: Runtime - Chat Execution
        Note over RCR: On chat request with<br/>model = agent key

        RCR->>RCR: mergeMcpServers() + resolve agents
        RCR->>Graph: AgentGraphManager.getSnapshot()
        Graph->>Graph: resolveAgentGraph(agents, defaultAgent)
        Note over Graph: Builds handoff + delegation<br/>function tools per agent

        Graph->>Orch: OpenAIAgentsOrchestrator
        Note over Orch: Converts AgentConfig →<br/>OpenAI Agents SDK Agent instances<br/>with handoffs[] and tools[]

        Orch->>LS: Runner.run(entryAgent, messages)
        Note over LS: Multi-turn execution:<br/>Agent calls tools → handoffs →<br/>specialist agents → tools → ...
        LS-->>Orch: Streaming response
        Orch-->>Admin: SSE events to chat UI
    end
